(ampolla)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"19","parent":"9","text":"Administración","guid":"","children":[{"id":"20","parent":"19","text":"Bolo directo + flush 10-20 mL SF 0.9%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"21","parent":"19","text":"Alternativa → aforar en 10 mL SF (1 mL adr + 9 mL SF) → más lento, menos preferido","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"22","parent":"9","text":"Momento de\\Nadministración","guid":"W3aL6j43YMZV3jx0RIut4Q","children":[{"id":"23","parent":"22","text":"Ritmos DESFIBRILABLES\\N(FV/TVSP)","guid":"WBCY1G4NG5JU20lsft2iNA","children":[{"id":"24","parent":"23","text":"Después de la 2a desfibrilación","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"25","parent":"23","text":"Luego cada 3-5 min","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"26","parent":"22","text":"Ritmos NO DESFIBRILABLES\\N(AESP/Asistolia)","guid":"JZjBCnyQwJMywgpeP2K5xw","children":[{"id":"27","parent":"26","text":"En cuanto se tenga acceso IV/IO → INMEDIATO","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"28","parent":"26","text":"Luego cada 3-5 min","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"29","parent":"9","text":"Guías europeas → retrasan adrenalina (después 3a descarga)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"30","parent":"0","text":"AMIODARONA →\\NAntiarrítmico intraparo","guid":"AZB44iaEf2k6jjktY7xOwQ","children":[{"id":"31","parent":"30","text":"Mecanismo\\Nde acción","guid":"ADtMOmdwf2oDAjRMP7OM6g","children":[{"id":"32","parent":"31","text":"Antiarrítmico clase III (efectos mixtos)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"33","parent":"31","text":"Bloqueo canales de potasio → prolonga potencial de acción y periodo refractario","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"34","parent":"31","text":"También bloquea canales de Na, Ca y receptores beta","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"35","parent":"31","text":"Objetivo → disminuir automaticidad y reentrada ventricular","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"36","parent":"30","text":"Indicación\\Nintraparo","guid":"TSPfZDvjrv0gF4K9YNRo9w","children":[{"id":"37","parent":"36","text":"FV/TVSP refractarias a desfibrilación + adrenalina","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"38","parent":"36","text":"Después de la 3a desfibrilación","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"39","parent":"30","text":"Dosis\\Nintraparo","guid":"MlUo0GM_FDEvBQdpOl2Dtw","children":[{"id":"40","parent":"39","text":"1a dosis → 300 mg IV/IO en bolo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"41","parent":"39","text":"2a dosis (opcional) → 150 mg después de 4a desfibrilación","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"42","parent":"30","text":"Presentación → 150 mg/3 mL (o 5 mL según marca)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"43","parent":"42","text":"Cargar 2 ampolletas para 1a dosis","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"44","parent":"30","text":"Administración","guid":"","children":[{"id":"45","parent":"44","text":"Bolo + flush 10-20 mL SF 0.9% o SG 5%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"46","parent":"44","text":"En intraparo SF es segura (incompatibilidad solo en infusión prolongada)","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"47","parent":"0","text":"LIDOCAÍNA →\\NAlternativa\\Nantiarrítmica intraparo","guid":"ch6riD6VpXRA2IKkTZU3cg","children":[{"id":"48","parent":"47","text":"Mecanismo\\Nde acción","guid":"fM0GOha2vxgSIOVTVN2fDg","children":[{"id":"49","parent":"48","text":"Antiarrítmico clase IB","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"50","parent":"48","text":"Bloqueo canales de sodio","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"51","parent":"48","text":"Reduce velocidad de despolarización y automaticidad ventricular","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"52","parent":"47","text":"Indicación","guid":"","children":[{"id":"53","parent":"52","text":"ALTERNATIVA a amiodarona (mismo nivel evidencia)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"54","parent":"52","text":"Después de 3a o 4a desfibrilación","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"55","parent":"52","text":"EXCEPCIÓN → paro por toxicidad anestésicos locales → NO usar lidocaína → usar amiodarona","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"56","parent":"47","text":"Dosis","guid":"","children":[{"id":"57","parent":"56","text":"1a dosis → 1-1.5 mg/kg IV/IO","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"58","parent":"56","text":"2a dosis → 50% de la primera (0.5-0.75 mg/kg)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"59","parent":"47","text":"Presentaciones y cálculo","guid":"","children":[{"id":"60","parent":"59","text":"Lidocaína 1% → 100 mg/10 mL (10 mg/mL)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"61","parent":"59","text":"Lidocaína 2% → 200 mg/10 mL (20 mg/mL)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"62","parent":"59","text":"Ejemplo 80 kg → al 1% = 8 mL, al 2% = 4 mL","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"63","parent":"47","text":"Ampolleta debe estar NUEVA (no reutilizar frascos abiertos de infiltración)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"64","parent":"0","text":"Resumen\\Nfármacos intraparo","guid":"BMPaq2b8Lr9Tu0FCKlybtQ","children":[{"id":"65","parent":"64","text":"Solo 3 fármacos acompañan RCP","guid":"","children":[{"id":"66","parent":"65","text":"1. Adrenalina","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"67","parent":"65","text":"2. Amiodarona O Lidocaína","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"68","parent":"64","text":"+ manejo etiológico (Hs y Ts)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"69","parent":"0","text":"AMIODARONA en\\Ntaquiarritmias estables","guid":"Y4zvUwZ9S6Bpv1V8ZR1oNQ","children":[{"id":"70","parent":"69","text":"Indicaciones","guid":"","children":[{"id":"71","parent":"70","text":"TV con pulso hemodinámicamente estable","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"72","parent":"70","text":"FA de respuesta ventricular rápida → si indicación control de ritmo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"73","parent":"70","text":"TSV refractaria a maniobras vagales + adenosina/calcioantagonistas","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"74","parent":"69","text":"Requisito →\\Npaciente ESTABLE","guid":"LQHLCSRNjqlI2bb3LT0XQw","children":[{"id":"75","parent":"74","text":"Sin hipotensión","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"76","parent":"74","text":"Sin alteración mental aguda","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"77","parent":"74","text":"Sin signos de shock","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"78","parent":"74","text":"Sin dolor torácico isquémico","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"79","parent":"74","text":"Sin datos de falla cardíaca","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"80","parent":"69","text":"Dosis en\\Ntaquiarritmia\\Nestable","guid":"C74OE0vb60Ns8KQtWOHtdw","children":[{"id":"81","parent":"80","text":"150 mg IV para 10 min","guid":"","children":[{"id":"82","parent":"81","text":"Aforar en 50-100 mL SG 5%","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"83","parent":"80","text":"Si no responde → repetir 150 mg para 10 min","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"84","parent":"80","text":"Si se inestabiliza → cardioversión eléctrica sincronizada","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"85","parent":"80","text":"NO en bolo → riesgo de bradiarritmia/asistolia","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"86","parent":"69","text":"Impregnación 24 horas\\N(post-cardioversión farmacológica)","guid":"B7-aQA0IJuo5tlZvOhTDEA","children":[{"id":"87","parent":"86","text":"Primeras 6 h → 1 mg/min (60 mg/h) = 360 mg","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"88","parent":"86","text":"Siguientes 18 h → 0.5 mg/min (30 mg/h) = 540 mg","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"89","parent":"86","text":"TOTAL 24 h → 900 mg","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"90","parent":"86","text":"Algunos protocolos → 10-15 mg/kg/24h (900-1050 mg)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"91","parent":"69","text":"Tiroides → sin contraindicación aguda (riesgo es a largo plazo)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"92","parent":"0","text":"ADENOSINA\\N→ TSV estable","guid":"cEc7G2i7Xdh0ckbHYmXmow","children":[{"id":"93","parent":"92","text":"Mecanismo\\Nde acción","guid":"J1EDTDVKyWsv-x4VJB4Jhg","children":[{"id":"94","parent":"93","text":"Actúa en receptores de adenosina del nodo AV","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"95","parent":"93","text":"Bloqueo momentáneo conducción AV","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"96","parent":"93","text":"Interrumpe circuito de reentrada de TSV","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"97","parent":"92","text":"Indicación","guid":"","children":[{"id":"98","parent":"97","text":"TSV de QRS estrecho, estable, que no respondió a maniobras vagales","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"99","parent":"97","text":"Maniobra vagal más efectiva → VALSALVA MODIFICADA con elevación pasiva piernas (~20% más éxito)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"100","parent":"92","text":"Dosis","guid":"","children":[{"id":"101","parent":"100","text":"1a dosis → 6 mg IV bolo rápido","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"102","parent":"100","text":"2a dosis → 12 mg si no responde","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"103","parent":"100","text":"CVC → 50% de la dosis (llega más rápido a aurícula)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"104","parent":"92","text":"Presentación → 6 mg/2 mL","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"105","parent":"92","text":"Técnica de\\Nadministración","guid":"TAGIhEIcA2l4-6iVUMVjLw","children":[{"id":"106","parent":"105","text":"Vía más proximal al corazón (antecubital)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"107","parent":"105","text":"Bolo rápido + flush inmediato 20 mL SF 0.9% (llave 3 vías)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"108","parent":"92","text":"PRECAUCIÓN","guid":"","children":[{"id":"109","parent":"108","text":"NO usar si sospecha síndrome de preexcitación (WPW)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"110","parent":"108","text":"Bloqueo AV puede liberar vía accesoria → TV","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"111","parent":"108","text":"Ante QRS ancho rápido regular → asumir TV hasta demostrar lo contrario","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"112","parent":"0","text":"VERAPAMILO →\\NAlternativa en TSV estable","guid":"KRgyKEy26dd7If7kDKUhew","children":[{"id":"113","parent":"112","text":"Mecanismo de acción","guid":"","children":[{"id":"114","parent":"113","text":"Calcioantagonista no dihidropiridínico","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"115","parent":"113","text":"Actúa en canales Ca cardíacos del nodo AV","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"116","parent":"113","text":"Disminuye conducción AV y prolonga periodo refractario","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"117","parent":"112","text":"Indicación → misma que adenosina (TSV estable)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"118","parent":"112","text":"Dosis → 5 mg IV lento (puede fraccionar 2.5 + 2.5 mg)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"119","parent":"112","text":"CONTRAINDICACIONES","guid":"","children":[{"id":"120","parent":"119","text":"Taquicardia ventricular","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"121","parent":"119","text":"TSV con vía accesoria (WPW) → mismo riesgo que adenosina","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"122","parent":"119","text":"Disfunción ventricular / IC → empeora contractilidad","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"123","parent":"0","text":"ATROPINA →\\NBradicardia inestable","guid":"UzQ1eGThVGBxwomxADYAgQ","children":[{"id":"124","parent":"123","text":"Mecanismo de acción","guid":"","children":[{"id":"125","parent":"124","text":"Antagonista competitivo receptores muscarínicos M2","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"126","parent":"124","text":"Bloquea parasimpático cardíaco → predomina simpático","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"127","parent":"124","text":"Aumenta automatismo nodo sinusal y conducción AV","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"128","parent":"123","text":"Dosis → 1 mg IV cada 3-5 min","guid":"","children":[{"id":"129","parent":"128","text":"Dosis máxima → 3 mg (3 dosis)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"130","parent":"128","text":"Presentación → 1 mg/1 mL","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"131","parent":"128","text":"Administración → bolo + flush 10-20 mL SF","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"132","parent":"123","text":"Conducta si no responde","guid":"","children":[{"id":"133","parent":"132","text":"NO repetir indefinidamente","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"134","parent":"132","text":"Escalar a marcapasos temporal","guid":"","children":[{"id":"135","parent":"134","text":"Transcutáneo (1a línea disponible)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"136","parent":"134","text":"Endovenoso","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"137","parent":"132","text":"Si no hay marcapasos → drogas cronotrópicas","guid":"","children":[{"id":"138","parent":"137","text":"Dopamina 5-20 mcg/kg/min","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"139","parent":"137","text":"Adrenalina 2-10 mcg/min","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"140","parent":"123","text":"Situaciones donde NO funciona","guid":"","children":[{"id":"141","parent":"140","text":"Bloqueos infrahisianos (QRS ancho)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"142","parent":"141","text":"BAV 2o grado Mobitz II","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"143","parent":"141","text":"BAV 3er grado (completo)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"144","parent":"141","text":"Puede empeorar → taquicardia auricular sin mejorar conducción ventricular","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"145","parent":"140","text":"Post-trasplante cardíaco → CORAZÓN DENERVADO","guid":"","children":[{"id":"146","parent":"145","text":"Sin inervación simpática → atropina inefectiva","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"147","parent":"145","text":"Requiere marcapasos","guid":"","children":[]}]}]}]},{"id":"148","parent":"0","text":"Errores frecuentes\\Nen ACLS","guid":"CS7jCTqcQKgtcxfFFOzxHA","children":[{"id":"149","parent":"148","text":"Dar fármacos sin RCP efectiva","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"150","parent":"148","text":"Retrasar desfibrilación por canalizar vía o administrar fármacos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"151","parent":"148","text":"Creer que adrenalina revive al paciente","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"152","parent":"148","text":"No identificar correctamente el ritmo cardíaco","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"153","parent":"148","text":"Detener compresiones para administrar medicamentos","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"154","parent":"0","text":"Criterios de compresiones\\Nde calidad","guid":"Bngr6xpju_Jtzt6TDjfGKw","children":[{"id":"155","parent":"154","text":"Centro del pecho, profundidad ≥5 cm","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"156","parent":"154","text":"Permitir recoil completo del tórax","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"157","parent":"154","text":"Frecuencia 100-120/min","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"158","parent":"154","text":"Interrupciones <10 seg","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"159","parent":"154","text":"EtCO2 >10-15 mmHg","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"160","parent":"154","text":"PAD arterial >20 mmHg (si línea arterial)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"161","parent":"0","text":"Perlas Clínicas","guid":"","children":[{"id":"162","parent":"161","text":"Adrenalina intraparo → efecto VASOPRESOR (alfa 1), NO revive","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"163","parent":"161","text":"Amiodarona/lidocaína → SOLO tras 3a desfibrilación, NUNCA antes","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"164","parent":"161","text":"Paro por anestésicos locales → NUNCA lidocaína → usar amiodarona","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"165","parent":"161","text":"Adenosina/verapamilo → CONTRAINDICADOS si sospecha WPW","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"166","parent":"161","text":"Atropina inútil en post-trasplante cardíaco (corazón denervado)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"167","parent":"161","text":"Atropina inútil en bloqueos infrahisianos (Mobitz II/BAV completo)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"168","parent":"161","text":"CVC → reducir adenosina al 50%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"169","parent":"161","text":"Amiodarona IV en bolo SOLO intraparo → fuera de paro siempre para 10 min","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"170","parent":"161","text":"Impregnación amiodarona 24h → 900 mg (360 + 540)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"171","parent":"161","text":"Valsalva modificada + elevación pasiva piernas → 20% más efectiva que Valsalva clásica","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"172","parent":"161","text":"GERIÁTRICA → considerar fragilidad en decisión de RCP y LET","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"173","parent":"161","text":"GERIÁTRICA → farmacocinética alterada en AM → ajustar según función renal/hepática","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"174","parent":"0","text":"VER TAMBIÉN","guid":"","children":[{"id":"175","parent":"174","text":"→ Paro Cardíaco - Algoritmo AHA (Emergencias)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"176","parent":"174","text":"→ Taquiarritmias (Cardiología)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"177","parent":"174","text":"→ Bradiarritmias y Marcapasos (Cardiología)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"178","parent":"174","text":"→ Sedación UCI (Farmacología)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"179","parent":"174","text":"→ Causas Reversibles Paro - Hs y Ts (Emergencias)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"180","parent":"0","text":"Referencias","guid":"","children":[{"id":"181","parent":"180","text":"1. Panchal AR, et al. 2020 AHA Guidelines for CPR and ECC. Circulation. 2020;142(16_suppl_2):S366-S468.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"182","parent":"180","text":"2. Soar J, et al. European Resuscitation Council Guidelines 2021: Adult ALS. Resuscitation. 2021;161:115-151.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"183","parent":"180","text":"3. Link MS, et al. Part 7: Adult ALS - 2015 AHA Guidelines Update. Circulation. 2015;132(18 Suppl 2):S444-64.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"184","parent":"180","text":"4. Kudenchuk PJ, et al. Amiodarone, Lidocaine, or Placebo in Out-of-Hospital Cardiac Arrest. N Engl J Med. 2016;374(18):1711-22.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"185","parent":"180","text":"5. Perkins GD, et al. A Randomized Trial of Epinephrine in Out-of-Hospital Cardiac Arrest (PARAMEDIC2). N Engl J Med. 2018;379(8):711-721.","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},"node_count":185,"relations":[],"cross_references":[],"specialty":"UCI/Medicina Crítica","folder":"Entidades clínicas/UCI-Medicina Crítica","filename":"Farmacos_ACLS_iPad","id":"map_2321","resolved_references":[],"title_raw":"Farmacos_ACLS_iPad"}